

Keywords:
		Search keywords: 	testbench sv array program port
 
Technical content:
		Title: 	      Usage of arrays in program port
		
		Objective:    To Demonstrate usage of arrays in program port

		Description: 	This shows an example of arrays in program port. Here the arrays are initialized in a different module and are passed into program via its ports
		
		Additional setup: None	
 
 To run the example:
      Using Makefile:
       	clean           -- To clean up the log files and executable of previous run
       	comp            -- To compile the design
        run             -- To run the design
        all             -- It does all the above steps.

     Using shell scripts:
        clean.csh       -- To clean up the log files and executable of previous run
        comp.csh        -- To compile the design
        run.csh         -- To run the design  
 
 Location Information:
		PATH: 			$VCS_HOME/doc/examples/testbench/sv/array_program_port
		DIAGRAMS: 		None
		Cross Reference:	$VCS_HOME/doc/UserGuide/svtb_tutorial.pdf & $VCS_HOME/doc/UserGuide/sv_lrm.pdf
